{"word":"Nehemiah","slug":"nehemiah","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>Nehemiah</b> <a href=\"#/H5166\">H5166</a> <br/> 1. Son of Hachaliah:<br/> - General references<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=16&chapter=1&verse=1'>Neh 1:1</a> <br/> - Cupbearer of Artaxerxes<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=16&chapter=1&verse=11'>Neh 1:11</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=16&chapter=2&verse=1'>Neh 2:1</a> <br/> - Is grieved over the desolation of his country<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=16&chapter=1&verse=11'>Neh 1:11</a> <br/> - Is sent by the king to rebuild Jerusalem<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=16&chapter=2&verse=8'>Neh 2:8</a> <br/> - Register of the people whom he led from Babylon<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=16&chapter=7'>Neh 7</a> <br/> - Register of the priests and Levites<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=16&chapter=12&verse=22'>Neh 12:22</a> <br/> - Rebuilds Jerusalem<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=16&chapter=2'>Neh 2</a> <br/> - His administration as ruler of the people<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=16&chapter=5'>Neh 5</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=16&chapter=8'>Neh 8</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=16&chapter=13'>Neh 13</a> <br/> 2. Two Jews who returned to Jerusalem from exile<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=15&chapter=2&verse=2'>Ezr 2:2</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=16&chapter=3&verse=16'>Neh 3:16</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=16&chapter=7&verse=7'>Neh 7:7</a>"}]}